title: Print, "Versailles, Gardens, Water Theatre", 1689
medium: Etching and engraving. Black ink on rolled paper.
inscribed:
Engraved on the plate at lower left:  "Peint par J. Cotelle" and on lower right:  "Et grave par L. Simonneau le Jeune 1689".
Inscription at lower center:  "Veue principale du theatre d'eau.  Dans le Jardin de Versailles"
description: Vertical rectangle:  At left and right foreground, the corners of tiers of bunches.  At center a raised stage with small lowered fountains at its forefront.  In the stage background and wings a central and two diagonal allees with cascades, arching and straight water jets and pyramidal trees, leading through the woods.

tombstone.epitaph: Print, "Versailles, Gardens, Water Theatre", 1689. Etching and engraving. Black ink on rolled paper.. 1972-7-20.
